Formation of the DnaJ-cr32-DnaK Complex Is ATP Depen-
dent. Next, we determined the relative affinity of o-32 for
DnaK or DnaJ. In the absence of ATP, when the molar ratio of DnaK, DnaJ, and or32 was approximately 1:1:1 in the incubation mixture, the majority of or32 was found in a
complex with DnaJ only (Fig. 2). This result demonstrates that DnaJ binds to ao32 much better than DnaK does. This
conclusion is consistent with the observation that, when the
amount of DnaK in the preincubation mixture was increased to 10-fold above that of o.32 and DnaJ, the formation of the DnaJ-or32-DnaK complex was readily seen. However, as expected, the bulk of DnaK sedimented in a position characteristic of that of a DnaK monomer (results not shown).
A surprising observation made during the course of this work was that the presence of ATP greatly stimulated the quantitative formation of DnaJ-cr32-DnaK complex even when the molar ratio of the three proteins was 1:1:1 (Fig. 2). For the efficient formation of this complex, the presence of ATP is absolutely required; i.e., when ATP was replaced either by its nonhydrolyzable analogs adenosine 5'-l,3, imido]triphosphate and adenosine 5'-[y-thioltriphosphate or by ADP, the DnaJ-or32-DnaK complex did not form. The DnaJ-cr32-DnaK complex must be fairly stable, since it is seen after a 24-hr centrifugation and persists at any concentration of ATP used in the gradient (ranging from 0 to 1 mM ATP; results not shown). In a control experiment, we were unable to demonstrate a direct physical interaction between DnaK and DnaJ under any of our experimental conditions.
When the third heat shock protein, GrpE, was included in the reaction mixture the extent of formation of the DnaJo'32-DnaK complex in the presence of ATP was essentially the same as that seen without GrpE. Furthermore, the GrpE protein was never seen to associate with the DnaJ-or32-DnaK complex (results not shown).
To further confi-m the validity of the results obtained by sedimentation analysis, we performed co-immunoprecipitation experiments as well. Using anti-DnaK antibodies, we were able to efficiently co-immunoprecipitate o,32 with DnaK protein only when either DnaJ and ATP was present or DnaJ

