eo Does Not Form a Stable Complex with DnaJ and DnaK. To determine whether the DnaJ-0.32-DnaK complex is specific for 0.32 we performed a series of experiments with the canonical E. coli a factor, 0.70. No evidence for a DnaJ-070, DnaK-o.70, or DnaJ-a070-DnaK complex could be seen after a 10-min preincubation at 37°C and glycerol gradient centrifugation (Fig. 4). Furthermore, in a competition experiment we established that the presence of a70 did not appreciably interfere with the formation of the DnaJ-0.32-DnaK complex
(Fig. 4).
